
[1]crowning

   CROWNING, ppr. Investing with a crown, or with royalty or supreme
   power; honoring with a wreath or with distinction; adorning; rewarding;
   finishing; perfecting.

   CROWNING, n.

   1. In architecture, the finishing of a member or any ornamental work.

   2. In marine language, the finishing part of a knot, or interweaving of
   the strands.
